{
  "texts": [
    "Trees were built from each orthogroup alignment using FastTree v2.1.10 (-nt -gtr) [102].",
    "Finally, BUSTED models were implemented using HyPhy [103].",
    "All Theobroma spp., including T. cacao, were used as the foreground while all other species were used as background.",
    "Results Meta-assembly of the cacao SCA 6 genomeThere are currently two reference genomes for cacao: the rare, fine-flavor cacao genotype Criollo B97-61/B2 [50,104], and one of the most widely cultivated cacao genotypes, Matina 1-6 [49].",
    "Neither genotype is highly resistant to Phytophthora spp."
  ]
}